==Funding==

2017: Slock.it raised about $2M in a seed funding round.<ref name=„funding“/>

Additional Information: In 2016, Slock.it created a Decetralized Autonomous Organization (DAO) called „The DAO“, a set of smart contracts operating on the Ethereum blockchain. Investors can send coins to the DAO and later vote on how to allocate the collected funds among several project proposals. The idea of Slock.it was to make a proposal of their Universal Sharing Network project to raise funds in this way. In the initial phase of The DAO, an attacker discovered a vulnerability in the code and managed to withdraw around 3.5M ETH (~$50M). Consequently, the hack lead to an ideological dissent in the community, with some people arguing in favor of the immutability of the ledger and others in favor of the invalidation of the hack. The disagreement lead to change in the consensus rules and consequently to a forking event (Ethereum and Ethereum Classic).
<ref name=„historydao“>https://blog.slock.it/the-history-of-the-dao-and-lessons-learned-d06740f8cfa5, accessed on 02.07.2018.</ref>

